<paragraph id="5848C94E2D7DFF90FF98F8DDFCA70C8A" blockId="21.[151,1436,1808,1976]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
This group is characterized by being more robust and of small to medium length (
<quantity id="9F0F64AB2D7DFF90FB21F8DDFB320C1A" box="[1070,1169,1808,1832]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“7 mm</quantity>
); the anterior portion of pronotum is very convex, red, with a strong transverse depression anterior to the blue base, and usually without prehumeral carinae; elytra have the apices more or less broadly, separately rounded, the posterior 
<number id="EE3FDB692D7DFF90FA09F895FAB70C42" box="[1286,1300,1880,1904]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number id="EE3FDB692D7DFF90FA12F895FA8A0C42" box="[1309,1321,1880,1904]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
with uniformly dense golden setae with the anterior margin of the golden area broadly emarginate medially along the suture, longer behind the humeri and at lateral margins.
</paragraph>
